BALTIMORE & OHIO R. R. CO., Appellant, v. Mayme A. BRETZ, Widow of Oliver B. Bretzr Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. January 3, 1929. No. 3890. See, also, 19 F.(2d) 960. John W. Huxley, Jr., of Wilmington, Del., for appellant. Frederick H. Warner and Clarence P. Sterner, both of Philadelphia, Pa., for ap-pellee.

Before BUFFINGTON and DAVIS, Circuit Judges, and Mc VICAR, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

The appeal in the above-entitled ease is dismissed. See Beaupre v. Noyes, 138 U. S. 397, 402, 11 S. Ct. 296, 34 L. Ed. 991.
